This paper deals with the problem of secret key agreement in the presence of an external eavesdropper, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of correlated sources, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.CC) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the capacity region, which is a concept in communication theory (cs.SI).
